<aside class="col-sm-5 col-md-4 col-sm-pull-7 col-md-pull-8"> <!-- Sidebar column -->
            <h2>Hosted by</h2>
            <% @show["hosts"].each do |host| %>
            <h3 class="host-name"><%= host["name"] %></h3>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-xs-3">
                <img class="img-responsive host-img" src="/images/hosts/<%= host["photo"] ? host["photo"] : "profile.png" %>"/>
              </div>
              <div class="col-xs-9">
                <ul class="list-unstyled host-links">
                  <% if host["website"] %><li><a href="http://<%= host["website"] %>"><i class="fa fa-globe fa-fw"></i> <%= host["website"] %> </a></li><% end %>
                  <% if host["twitter"] %><li><a href="http://twitter.com/<%= host["twitter"] %>"><i class="fa fa-twitter fa-fw"></i> <%= host["twitter"] %></a></li><% end %>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <% end %>

            <div class="support-sidebar">
              <h3>The Show Must Go On</h3>
              <p>If you like what we're doing, then help us keep the lights on and the episodes coming!</p>
              <p><a href="/support" class="btn btn-lg btn-support"><i class="fa fa-thumbs-up fa-fw"></i> Support The Show</a></p>
            </div>

            <div class="press">
              <h3>Praise for Flipping Tables</h3>
              <div class="quote">
                <img class="pull-left quote-img" src="/images/assets/quote.png" />
                <p>If you're looking for nerds opining about technology, throw a dart at iTunes. With Flipping Tables, David &amp; Michael provide an often missing ingredient: perspective. Even when they're full of shit, they're still smarter than you.</p>
                <p class="attribution"><a href="http://matthewdjordan.com/">- Matthew D. Jordan</a></p>
              </div>
              <div class="quote">
                <img class="pull-left quote-img" src="/images/assets/quote.png" />
                <p>Flipping Tables cuts the fat - they simply ask the same questions you do, then dust it with humor and an agnostic perspective.</p>
                <p class="attribution"><a href="http://matthewdjordan.com/">- Matthew D. Jordan</a></p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </aside> <!-- End of Sidebar -->
